## âš™ï¸ 1. Setup Instructions

### ğŸ”Œ Create the Shared Network (only once)

```bash
docker network create global_network

ğŸš€ Start Any Service
Each service lives in a separate folder. To start any of them:

cd ~/Docker-Services/<service-name>
docker compose --env-file .env up -d

Replace <service-name> with one of: mysql, mongodb, redis, phpmyadmin.


ğŸ“„ 2. Laravel .env Configuration

ğŸ”¸ MySQL
DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=mysql_global
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=your_database
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=pass


ğŸ”¸ MongoDB
DB_CONNECTION=mongodb
DB_HOST=mongodb_global
DB_PORT=27017
DB_DATABASE=your_database
DB_USERNAME=admin
DB_PASSWORD=adminpass


ğŸ”¸ Redis
REDIS_HOST=redis_global
REDIS_PORT=6379
REDIS_PASSWORD=secretpass

# Optional
QUEUE_CONNECTION=redis
CACHE_DRIVER=redis
SESSION_DRIVER=redis


ğŸ”¸RABBITMQ
QUEUE_CONNECTION=rabbitmq
RABBITMQ_HOST=rabbitmq_global
RABBITMQ_PORT=5672
RABBITMQ_USER=admin
RABBITMQ_PASSWORD=adminpass
RABBITMQ_VHOST=/



